# Payroll — single owner-employee

## Treatment

- Owner is an **employee (T4 + RL-1)**, not self-employed payroll.
- Pay runs live in `payroll/runs/YYYY-MM-DD_pay-period.csv`.
- Remittance records in `payroll/remittances/`.

## Each pay run must include

- Gross pay, vacation pay (if applicable), taxable benefits
- Employee deductions: income tax, CPP, EI, QPIP (if applicable), Québec tax
- Employer portions: matching CPP/EI/QPIP employer shares, employer contributions
- Net pay and payment date / method

## Equity vs payroll

| Type | Where it goes |
|------|----------------|
| Salary / wages | Payroll expense + liabilities |
| Dividends | Equity / retained earnings — **not** payroll |
| Shareholder loan | Liability account — track repayments |
| Owner contribution | Equity |

## Slips & remittances

- Draft T4/RL-1 summaries in `payroll/year-end/` — CPA files.
- Track CRA RP and Revenu Québec TPZ remittance due dates; never mark paid without owner confirmation.

## Rates

- Use current CRA and Revenu Québec tables for the tax year in `company/profile.md`.
- If rates are uncertain, cite the source URL and year; do not guess.
